       @Column(name = &quot;Id&quot;)
        private int parentId;
    }

then you save parent object

    Parent createdParent = parentRepository.save(parent);

returned createdParent contains auto generated *Parent ID* Use it for setting above parentId field inside Child entity. like below.

    child.setParentId(createdParent.getId());

then save child entity, like.

     childRepository.save(child);

